<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="85" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/10403</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The French High Commissioner</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_TAPGA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tardieu</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                    the Assistant to the Counselor for the Department of State</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_AG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Auchincloss</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 29891</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1918</hi>.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Counselor</hi>: Confirming my
                                conversation with you, of August 29, I beg to state that I have been
                                instructed by my Government to ascertain whether the American
                                Government would be willing to appoint a representative to an
                                inter-Allied blockade committee to be constituted in Paris for the
                                discussion of economic questions relating to Spain and
                                Switzerland.</p>
                            <p>This proposed committee would be on the same lines as the one at
                                present existing in London for northern European neutrals.</p>
                            <pb facs="0160" n="994" xml:id="pg_994"/>
                            <p>My Government is of opinion that such an organization would
                                materially strengthen and coordinate inter-Allied blockade action in
                                Spain and Switzerland.</p>
                            <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the High Commissioner: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBE1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Billy</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>